article.headline: Fairleigh Dickinson 70, Wagner 65
article.story: HACKENSACK, N.J. -- Sean Baptiste scored 26 points and Fairleigh Dickinson rallied past Wagner 70-65 on Thursday night. Baptiste scored six of his team's final nine points as the Knights (9-17, 8-5 Northeast Conference) made a 9-2 run to end the game. With the Knights trailing 63-61 with 4:08 to play, Baptiste hit a jumper, then made a steal and scored on a layup to give his team a 65-63 lead with 2:51 to go. After two free throws by Wagner's Doug Elwell cut the lead to 67-65, Baptiste hit a basket with 21 seconds remaining to seal the victory. Wagner (4-22, 2-11) led 33-29 at halftime and built a 13-point lead at 52-39 with 13:45 to play after a 3-pointer by Danny Mundweiler. But the Knights went on a 22-8 run to grab a 61-60 lead with 4:28 to play. Mundweiler scored 18 points, Tyler Murray added 17 and Elwell had 12 for the Seahawks, who lost their third straight game.
